OL,6,FSenior railway staff have described
OL,7,Fthe incident as "reckless", adding
OL,8,Fthat "the entrance to the level
OL,9,Fcrossing displays a red warning light
OL,10,Fwhen it is unsafe to cross, along with
OL,11,Fbarriers to keep people safe which the
OL,12,Fperson ignored."
OL,14,FNatalie Stretton is the head of
OL,15,Foperational risk for the Central route
OL,16,Fat Network Rail. She said: "There's
OL,17,Fnever any excuse for this kind of
OL,18,Freckless behaviour. The difference of
OL,19,Fjust a few seconds could have led to
OL,20,Ftragedy and I can't downplay the
OL,21,Fdanger they put themselves in."
